Data file handling in java for Text files

Java harr file ko ek stream of bytes ki tarah dekhta hai
Harr OS file ke end ko identify karne ke liye ya toh EOF use karta hai ya total size of file.

File streams are used to perform input and output operations on a file.

Streams input and output operations are performed in a sequential order.
Streams inputing and outputing bytes are known as byte-based streams.
Streams inputing and outputing characters are known as character-based streams.

Byte based streams are used to perform input and output operations on Binary files.
Character based streams are used to perform input and output operations on Text files.